# Group Capture Points

The consumer capture points


## Capture point [/capture/{campaignguid}/]

### Submits consumer data to the campaign  [POST]
This returns status 200 if the data was submitted with no issues
Status 206 is returned if one or more look up fields where incorrectly passed (e.g. marital status, province, etc). The record is still saved but without the offending value.
Status 400 is returned if one or more mandatory fields are missing (campaign guid, email or mobile).
Status 500 is returned if the user cannot be saved due to a server error

+ Response 200 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)
+ Response 206 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    ``` 
        {  
        "FailReason":Meaningful fail message, listing missing content"
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    ``` 
        {  
        "FailReason":Message lists missing field"

        }
+ Response 500 (application/json;charset=UTF-8)

    ``` 
        {  
        "FailReason":Meaningful fail message"

        }
